Objective

To extract and clean book data from a publicly available website using Python and BeautifulSoup, producing a structured dataset suitable for analytics.

What Was Done

Scraped all pages of BooksToScrape.com

Extracted titles, prices, ratings, stock status, and product URLs

Cleaned corrupted text and transformed prices to numeric values

Exported results to a clean CSV file

Key Results

1,000+ books scraped

100% clean, analysis-ready dataset

UTF-8 handling ensured no garbled characters

Successfully collected consistent and reliable structured data

Business Value

This type of workflow can be applied to:

Competitor price monitoring

Product catalog analytics

Market research

E-commerce dashboards

Conclusion

This project demonstrates proficiency in web scraping, data cleaning, and pipeline automation key skills for Data Analysts and Data Engineers.
